‹g¬]<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1164";s:4:"name";s:12:"Fibromyalgia";s:4:"slug";s:12:"fibromyalgia";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1164";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:3265:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">Fibromyalgia is a condition that causes widespread pain along with the muscular parts of the body. It is accompanied by sleep, fatigue, and mood swings. Women have a higher chance of developing the disease. Although there is no cure for fibromyalgia, certain medications and lifestyle changes can help. Fibromyalgia can cause:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fatigue</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Pain all over the body</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cognitive imbalance</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Irritable bowel syndrome</span></li>
</ul>
<span style="font-weight: 400;">Doctors are still left out of the loop on the cause of fibromyalgia, but they think that combination of some factors such as genetics, infections,¬† physical or emotional trauma, and lots more may cause it.</span>

<b>Thriving With Fibromyalgia</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Certain lifestyle changes can play a huge role in fibromyalgia symptoms. Here are 5 of them:</span>

<b>Get a massage: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Massage can effectively help reduce symptoms of fibromyalgia such as swelling and stiffness.</span>

<b>Manage your stress: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">The inability to deal with stress can worsen the symptoms of fibromyalgia. Relaxation techniques like deep breathing can help you relieve stress.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Try to dedicate some time to do activities that let you relieve stress. For example, you can go swimming, keep aside an hour or two for reading or take a visit to family and friends.</span>

<b>Maintain a regular sleep routine: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sleeping for at least 8 hours every night is a good way to combat the symptoms of fibromyalgia. For better sleep, try breathing exercises or meditation. If you still have a hard time sleeping, go see your doctor for guidance.</span>

<b>Stay conscious of your weight: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">As we know, being overweight can cause more harm than good to the body.</span>

<b>Stay hydrated: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Drink plenty of water. Avoid alcohol.</span>

<b>Eat right: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Try out the whole grain. They contain fibers and nutrients which are beneficial to the heart.</span>

<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay, Motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done pathbreaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, ‚ÄúIllness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.‚Äù</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of Fibromyalgia is: </span><b>Resistance to new experiences. Muscles represent our ability to move in life.</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the ways of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations.¬†</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for healing Fibromyalgia is: </span><b>I lovingly release the past. They are free and I'm free. All is well in my heart now</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"0";}}